name: WordAbbreviation
statement: You are given a String[] words, each element of which is a single word. Return a String[] where the i-th element is the abbrevation for the i-th word. The abbreviation for a word is its shortest non-empty prefix that is not a prefix of any other given word. The constraints will guarantee that it is possible to find an abbreviation for all the given words.
constraints: words will contain between 1 and 50 elements, inclusive.
Each element of words will contain between 1 and 50 characters, inclusive.
Each element of words will only contain lowercase letters ('a'-'z').
No element of words will be a prefix of another element of words.

examples.comment: A single character is enough.
It's possible that the abbreviation is the same as the original word.
